name: GPS
effect: Indicates the distance in number of jumps from the current article to all articles to visit, with the preferred link to use.

name: BACK
effect: Allows the player to return to the previous article when stuck or landing on an article with no outgoing links.

name: TELEPORT
effect: Allows the player to teleport to an article that is 2 links away from one of the articles to visit.

name: MINE
effect: Traps an article. If an opponent lands on the mined article or an article linked to it, they are sent back 5 articles in their visit history.

name: SNAIL
effect: Forces the player to stay on the article for at least 1 minute without being able to click on any links.

name: ERASER
effect: Removes the most recently visited target article from the player's progress, forcing them to revisit it.

name: DISORIENTATOR
effect: Sends the player randomly to any article on Wikipedia.

name: DICTATOR
effect: Forces the player to immediately visit one of the target articles, ignoring any other articles visited along the way.
